Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager, Facilities &amp; Administration Pickering , ON Description The team at the Pickering Public Library are collaborators and innovators. We embrace change, diversity and inclusion. We understand “the why” behind what we do, and we put library clients first. Our hope is that when anyone visits the Pickering Public Library, whether in person or online, they don’t just walk through a door. Instead, they step into a space that offers everyone possibility. Reveals potential. And provides community for all. Does this sound like a workplace that aligns with the contributions you want to make in your career? The Pickering Public Library has a full-time opening for a Manager, Facilities &amp; Administration.Summary:Under the direction of the Director, Corporate Services and Collections, this position is responsible for overseeing the day-to-day facilities operations, which includes building maintenance, repairs, furniture, equipment, fleet vehicles as well as facilities project management, ensuring the library provides welcoming, safe, inclusive and fresh library spaces. This role will also lead the administrative staff, manage budgets, deliver financial reporting and ensure accurate and complete financial systems and processes (including budgets, accounting, procurement, payments, asset management and daily operations) for the Pickering Public Library. Salary: Annual salary range starting at $97,260.80 (including comprehensive benefits package and OMERS pension plan)Hours: 35 per week Telework arrangement possible in accordance with the Library’s Telework PolicyThe Successful Applicant:Will be responsible for the management and development of employees within Facilities &amp; Administration – who are responsible for ensuring that all library facilities are clean, well maintained, safe, secure, and welcoming, ensuring accessibility of physical facilities. Including hiring, supervising, evaluating, and coaching direct reports.Wil assume responsibility for the library’s financial system, procurement practices, inventory and property management, preparing annual operating and capital budgets.Will provide leadership as a member of the Corporate Services and Collections team which collaborates to provide relevant, responsive, equitable, accessible and transformational Library services for our community through collections, IT, business intelligence, facilities and finance.Demonstrates excellence in interpersonal and communication skills, responsible for overseeing and providing services to customers with a lens to identify, prevent and remove systemic barriers to equity in Library services.Will be responsible for applying an inclusive, equity-driven lens in work that contributes to PPL being an inclusive Library for our community and an inclusive organization for our staff, volunteers, and stakeholders.Applicants Must Have:Bachelor’s Degree completion.Three years of relevant leadership or management experience.Ontario Class G driver's license in good standingDemonstrated proficiency in:Office Suite (Intermediate)Email (Advanced)Internet (Advanced)Mobile Devices and Apps (Intermediate)ILS (Intermediate)Social Media (Intermediate)Scanning, Printing (Intermediate) We thank all applicants for their interest. Please note that only applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. Successful applicants must be prepared to undergo a satisfactory Criminal Records Check (CPIC vulnerable sector search) as a condition of employment. Please note that job offers will only be made upon successful completion of all background checks. Qualified candidates may submit a detailed cover letter and resume on or before September 9th, 2024 to: Human Resources Associate By Email: hr@pickering.ca Human Resources Department By Fax: 905.420.4638 One The Esplanade Online: https://pickeringlibrary.ca/job-opportunities/ Pickering, ONL1V 6K7 Compensation Annual salary range starting at $97,260.80 Closes: 9 September, 2024 Pickering Public Library Pickering , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
