policies.Ensures that all business conducted by the library and the Board complies with provincial legislation. Please review the detailed job description at sparwoodlibrary.ca for full details including desired qualifications, knowledge, skills and abilities. For this interim role, we welcome applications from candidates with some combination of our desired education and experience. Compensation: $41/hour. This six-month opportunity offers two weeks of paid vacation. This is a transitional time for the Sparwood Public Library, and the Interim Director will be essential to stabilize operations and ensure quality library service to the community. Upon successful completion of the six-month term, this position has the potential become a permanent role. HOW TO APPLY TO THIS EXPRESSION OF INTEREST OPPORTUNITY: Please email your cover letter and resume to director@sparwoodlibrary.ca no later than 5pm MDT Tuesday September 10, 2024. To be considered for this position, your email and resume must clearly demonstrate how you meet the requirements listed above and as outlined in the job description.The successful candidate will be required to complete a vulnerable sector criminal record check. The cost of this screening will be reimbursed by SPLA. Compensation $41/hour Closes: 10 September, 2024 Sparwood Public Library Sparwood , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
