brary website and social mediaAssists with statistical documentation of the use of library collections, programs and services.Other duties as assigned. Conditions of Employment Successful incumbent must complete a criminal record check prior to commencing work; Required to join CUPE Local #561; Required to work at any branch in the Coquitlam Public Library system as well as Library Link. Requirements Completion of a Library Technician diploma.Sound knowledge of library methods, procedures and tools applicable to the work.Sound knowledge of the Dewey decimal classification system, the current international cataloguing rules, and the local cataloguing standards, procedures and practices as related to the work performed.Ability to assist the public in the access, location and use of a wide variety of internal and external source material, technical resources, and bibliographic tools. Strong command of English communication skills, including verbal and written a necessity. Well-developed interpersonal skills required as this position works with various library staff and the public. Ability to operate computer terminal and other library equipment. Strong keyboarding skills required. Travel between branches is required. Shifts may be assigned at any branch. What We Offer In addition to an excellent compensation package, we provide a working environment that supports knowledge, innovation and fun. With a strong focus on safety, we strive to inspire learning and service to our diverse community. If you have a proven commitment to providing exceptional customer service in a team environment, with a friendly, patient and outgoing personality, we are interested in hearing from you. TO APPLY FOR THIS POSITION: Please send an email to humanresources@coqlibrary.cawith your cover letter and resume attached in PDF format. The subject line must include the job code. If you are applying for more than one posting, only one email is required; however, please include all applicable job 